---
title: Honey Thyme Pork Tenderloin with Roasted Potatoes & Green Beans
description: A honey-based sauce may sound like something that goes with dessert, but mild-tasting pork loves a sweet sauce too, especially one that has a few savory elements added to the mix. In this recipe, you’ll be folding an extra-large drizzle of honey into a rich, savory pan sauce, then spooning it onto pork tenderloin. (We recommend spooning it on the roasted potatoes and side of green beans, too!)
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/62163df726affc043e76f4ef-6b768aaf.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/honey-thyme-pork-tenderloin-62163df726affc043e76f4ef-fe1689aa.pdf
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/honey-thyme-pork-tenderloin-62163df726affc043e76f4ef
time required: 30 minutes
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 480 kcal
  fat: 22 g
